metadata.name: View #98
metadata.description:
Generative art is rarely representational, this work seeks to explore what can be achieved by an algorithm with the medium of pixel art. 

The algorithm generates a 200x200 pixel art image showing a view from a window over the sea. There are three backdrops available, all completely procedural. No baked-in sprites were used. I hope that the love that went into making it is clear.


Please enjoy the view.

metadata.name: 空-sora- #109
metadata.description:
Japanese word Sora(空) means Sky.

An abstract painting of a landscape with sky.
Drawing based on mathematics fractal.

Top has 3 variations.
Bottom has 4 variations.
Cloud has 3 variations.
Background has White or Black 2 variations.
Stroke has ON or OFF 2 variations.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [f] to switch full screen on and off
- Press [s] to download a PNG file with windowsize
- Press [l] to download a PNG file with large size 3200 x 4800 pixel (wait a minutes)

Create with p5.js
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Abstract Hedonism #180
metadata.description:
Abstraction is the beauty of pure geometry and mathematics.

That project was inspired by fathers of minimalism and suprematism, such as the : El Lissitzky, Kazimir Malevich, Pit Mondrian, Paul Klee, etc.

My main goal was to learn how to work with Perlin noise, implement it in different formats and compositions.

Project contains:

•Various formats and orientations of the canvas: from 100 to 1900 pixels
•Carefully selected color palettes with rare BLACK ones
•Fully random animation
•Press "s" to save .png


Made in P5.js by @Georginerous
